-- Credit Suisse Hires Gaertner for Technology Corporate Finance
-- B y   S e r e n a   S a i t t o
-- 2012-04-10T20:09:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-10/credit-suisse-hires-gaertner-for-technology-corporate-finance.html
Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  hired Chris Gaertner from  Bank of America Corp. (BAC)  as head of global corporate
finance for the technology group based in San Francisco.  Gaertner, who led the technology group at Merrill Lynch &
Co. from 2006 to 2008, will start at the Zurich-based bank in
July, according to an internal memo.  Gaertner advised Autonomy Corp. Plc on its sale to Hewlett
Packard Co. and Lawson Software Inc. on its $1.9 billion
acquisition by Golden Gate Capital Corp. He will report to Mark Simonian and David Wah, the bank’s global co-head of
telecommunications, media and technology, according to the memo.  The New York Times DealBook reported Gaertner’s move
earlier today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Serena Saitto in  New York  at 
 ssaitto@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
